Inspection Process :
Inspection take about two to three hours , with most of our time being spent on the major components of the house: 

• Foundation/Exterior

profile:
Talk to a professionally trained, certified, experienced air quality consultant today. 613-821-0035

At Indoor Air Quality Ottawa, our strength is identifying the source of problems so you can thrive in a healthy environment.

Identifying an odour is secondary to determining why it occurred in the first place. Our strength lies in finding the source – mould, sewer gas, combustion spillage, chemical off-gassing – then ensuring it won’t come back again by specifying remediation solutions that fix the root cause of the problem.

IAQ Ottawa will identify your air quality concerns and deliver professional, cost-effective, permanent solutions. Our professionally trained consultants have provided solutions to all types of air quality conditions since 2003. 

“6000+ residential inspections. 700+ commercial inspections”

For more information, please visit www.iaqo.ca or email us at info@iaqo.ca

profile:
About Us
My father, Valmont Bérubé started our general contracting company more than 35 years ago. And for over 15 years now we have been leveraging this wealth of knowledge by focusing on providing professional home inspection services in Ottawa and the surrounding areas. I’ve been in the construction business since 1994 and a building inspector since 2005.

As part of our commitment to supporting our Ottawa community, we shared our knowledge through our informative television series on Rogers cable called 2×4. For over 9 years, we provided our audience with great tips, tutorials, manufacturer tours and relevant news to help you improve your home, health and safety.

Our​ ​knowledge​ ​sharing​ ​continued​ ​as​ ​we​ ​provided​ ​carpentry​ ​education​ ​at​ ​La​ ​Cité​ ​collégiale, teaching​ ​men​ ​and​ ​women​ ​on​ ​home​ ​construction​ ​as​ ​they​ ​work​ ​towards​ ​their​ ​carpentry certificates. Home​ ​safety​ ​is​ ​an​ ​important​ ​topic​ ​for​ ​us.​ ​I​ ​apply​ ​my​ ​knowledge​ ​and​ ​experience​ ​as​ ​a​ ​former volunteer​ ​firefighter​ ​and​ ​fire​ ​code​ ​inspector​ ​for​ ​the​ ​City​ ​of​ ​Clarence-Rockland​ ​to​ ​all​ ​our​ ​home inspections. My​ ​father​ ​passed​ ​away​ ​in​ ​2013​​ ​​and,​ ​in​ ​his​ ​name,​ ​I​ ​Continue​ ​to​ ​pursue​ ​our​ ​shared​ ​vision​ ​to providing​ ​honest​ ​quality​ ​services​ ​to​ ​our​ ​local​ ​community.

services:
Our Services
I bring over 25 years of industry experience in building and inspecting homes. My inspections are thorough and also include important tips on how to maintain your home and suggestions on dos and don’ts. A written report is handed to the buyers on site as soon as the inspection is completed. The Ottawa real estate market can be demanding sometimes and getting a same day report is extremely valuable. Being in construction an approximate cost of repairs can also be done although this can be seen as being outside of a home inspection scope but I’m here to please and want my buyers to make the most informed decision possible.

Home Inspections
I offer a series of personalized home inspection services.

Cost of inspections can very between 250$ to 500$ or more depending on the type of building and amount of units in buildings.
Payment methods can be cheque, debit, credit or e-transfers on the day of the inspection..

Pre-Sales Inspection
A home is an important and stressful purchase. Having a qualified inspector review your future new property help provide you with the assurance. Knowing what you’re getting into and how to maintain your biggest investment is crucial.

New Build Inspection
Just because it’s new doesn’t mean you shouldn’t have it inspected. Having an unbiased 3 rd-party inspector can go a long way in ensuring builders are delivering the product you’re expecting and deserve.

Multi-Unit or Investment Property
Partner with us to enjoy the benefits of having us ensure your property portfolio is regularly inspected to identify issues early on.

Infrared TherImal Imaging
Is another inspection service that we offer to get an in depth view of your home.

Below are just a few of the elements we cover during our thorough inspections:

● General Exterior:Grading, window wells, eavestrough, sidings, soffit & fascia, trim, roof covers, chimney, garage, steps.
● Heating:Heating plant, fresh air, network, baseboard heating.
● Plumbing: Service, supply, water heater, waste drainage, sump.
● Structural: Foundation, roof sheathing, walls, interior support, basement water problems, roof support.
● Electrical: Feed, service, panels, wiring.
● Insulation: Type of insulation, attic venting, crawlspace, vapour barrier, weather stripping & sealing.
● General Interior: Finish, floors, stairs, doors, window, fireplaces, fans, outlets, heat distribution, plumbing fixtures, smoke detectors and attic

services:
BUYER’S INSPECTION
Buying a home is a major decision, and you should make that decision only after understanding the home’s condition, repair needs, and future maintenance requirements fully. During the Buyer’s Inspection, we find the home’s defects and help you understand the property so that you can make wise and confident decisions should you choose to purchase.

New Construction Inspection Service
NEW CONSTRUCTION WARRANTY INSPECTIONS
We offer New Construction Phase Inspections for new homes at the following important times:

Pre-Delivery: we inspect the new home one or two weeks prior to the client taking possession
A 30-Day Inspection
A One-Year Inspection
Pre Listing Inspection
PRE-LISTING INSPECTION
Home inspections can be just as important for sellers as for buyers. During a Pre-Listing Inspection, we will show sellers the repairs they can make before listing to make the home more attractive to buyers. We will also give them the information they need to communicate and negotiate clearly.

New Construction Inspection Service
 THERMAL IMAGING INSPECTION
This inspection service will utilize infrared thermography to check for issues such as plumbing leaks inside a home and exterior moisture intrusion. We’ll also do a scan to look for electrical hotspots and other energy issues that you should be aware of.


HOME MAINTENANCE INSPECTION
It is normal for small issues to arise in the home. However, small issues that are left unnoticed and unaddressed can quickly turn into large issues that are expensive to repair. This can be avoided by scheduling a Home Maintenance Inspection. We will thoroughly inspect the home for the small repairs you can make now to save yourself time and money later.

Outside In Home Inspection, serving Ottawa and surrounding area.
A thorough home inspection prior to buying any house is the best protection against possible major repairs after the purchase. A good home inspection will look closely at every aspect of a house, from its plumbing and electrical systems to things as simple as bathroom fans and garage doors, in order to be sure that everything is working correctly. Any problems that the home inspector finds can then be dealt with before the purchase of the home and may result in saving the home buyer hundreds, if not thousands, of dollars later on.

profile:
We have developed one the best reputation serving the Ottawa community over the past decade.  We value that reputation!  It’s that reputation that is at stake on every inspection.

* Attention to detail is important when making an investment decision

* Our job is to provide all the facts needed to make this important decision.
   
* We meet your needs by identifying all inspection issues and put them in perspective.

*  Our inspectors have a background in engineering (B. Eng), energy assessment and home renovation.

*  We utilize state of the art tools such as an infrared camera, moisture meter, and eye stick.


EcoHome Inspectors is dedicated to providing you the highest quality professional home inspections in the industry. Our inspections and reports meet and exceed industry standards and are conducted by certified home inspectors who are committed to constant improvement through on-going training.

We produce a thorough and unbiased inspection of the property by providing objective and confidential inspections in a prompt and courteous manner. Our experience, hard work and attention to detail will make EcoHome Inspectors your first choice in home inspectors.

profile:
Francis Caza, RHI (Registered Home Inspector) is the chair of the Ottawa chapter of the Ontario Association of Home Inspectors (OAHI). He has worked in home construction in Ottawa-Gatineau for over 30 years. It is this expertise that Francis brings to your home inspection.

Francis has received his Canadian National Radon Proficiency Program (C-NRPP) certification. This means that he is fully qualified to test for radon gas in your home.

We're committed to providing solid information in an interactive report.
